                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>By an exchange of notes signed at Guatemala City, January 7 and 8, 1952, and
                    entered into force on the latter date, Guatemala agreed to the application of
                    sections 511 (b) and 515 of the Mutual Security Act of 1951 to the technical
                    cooperation programs operated in Guatemala by the United States. The notes were
                    transmitted to the Department of State under cover of despatch 820, dated
                    February 13, 1952, not printed (814.00 <gloss target="#t_TA1"
                    >TA</gloss>/2–1352). For text of the notes, see <hi rend="italic">United States
                        Treaties and Other International Agreements</hi> (UST), volume 3 (part 4),
                    page 4728, or Department of State Treaties and Other International Acts Series
                    (TIAS) No. 2634; for text of the Mutual Security Act (Public Law 165), approved
                    October 10, 1951, see 65 Stat. 373.</p>
            </div>
